    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A subpoena commanding his at\ntendance before the Spokane coun-\nty grand jury has been served on\nLouis w. Hill, president of the\nGreat Northern railroad. Personal\nservice was secured on him at his\nOffice in st. Paul last Saturday by\nDeputy Sheriff S. d. Doak, who was\nin the east on other business for\nthe state and dropped into st. Paul\nto leave the little reminder with\nMr.. Hill that thesSpokane county\ngrand jury was still doing business\nat the old stand.\n\n\nThis was the first subpoena\nserved on Hill in person, as in the\ncase of the former subpoena it was\nleft at his Office by Doak, to be\nread by Hill at his leisure. In or\nder that Hill may not be detained"
    }
